    "answer": "Here are my detailed findings from investigating the codebase:\n\n## Findings\n\n### Root Cause\nThe markdown tab and attachments tab in `TaskDetailPanel.axaml` have `ScrollViewer` elements with only **8px of bottom padding** (`Padding=\"8,14,8,8\"` and `Padding=\"8,4,8,8\"` respectively). This insufficient bottom inset causes the last line(s) of content to be partially cut off when scrolled to the bottom, because the content's final text line (with `LineHeight=\"21\"`) or image sits flush against the scroll container's bottom boundary.\n\n### Already-Fixed Reference Pattern\nThe developers previously solved this exact bug in `StageInputView.axaml` (lines 98-105) and `StageOutputView.axaml` (lines 111-117) for their parsed/rendered views. Those files contain an explicit comment:\n```\n<!-- Inset lives on the content (not ScrollViewer.Padding) so the bottom\n     gap is part of the measured extent and the last item stays reachable. -->\n```\nThey use `Margin=\"8,8,8,16\"` on the inner content (`ItemsControl`) \u2014 the extra **16px bottom margin** on the content itself ensures the scroll extent extends past the last element. The same fix was **not applied** to `TaskDetailPanel.axaml`.\n\n### All Affected Areas in TaskDetailPanel.axaml\n1. **Markdown tab \u2013 Read-only view** (lines 144-152): `ScrollViewer` with `Padding=\"8,14,8,8\"` wrapping a `TextBlock`.\n2. **Context tab** (lines 204-213): `ScrollViewer` with `Padding=\"8,18,8,8\"` wrapping a `TextBlock`.\n3. **Attachments tab** (lines 225-268): `ScrollViewer` with `Padding=\"8,4,8,8\"` wrapping an `ItemsControl` containing images and text.\n\n### Important Note on Stage 1 Options\nThe ideation options referencing web-CSS properties (`scroll-padding-bottom`, `::after` pseudo-elements, `scrollIntoView`) are **not applicable** \u2014 this is an **Avalonia UI** application (`.axaml` files), not a web app. The fix must use Avalonia's layout properties (`Padding`/`Margin` on the content element).\n\n### No Auto-Scroll Logic\nThere is no auto-scroll-to-bottom or programmatic scroll logic in the codebase (grep for `ScrollIntoView`, `ScrollToBottom`, `ScrollChanged` returned no matches), so the issue is purely layout-based.\n\n### Correct Approach\nFollow the already-established pattern: move breathing room from `ScrollViewer.Padding` (bottom) to **`Margin` on the inner content element** (or add an explicit bottom margin/padding to the content). This ensures the last line is reachable by scrolling. The consistent fix would be to add `Margin=\"...,...,...,16\"` or sufficient bottom padding to the inner content of each affected tab, matching the `16px` bottom margin used in StageInputView/StageOutputView.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"findings\": \"The markdown tab read-only view (TaskDetailPanel.axaml lines 144-152) and attachments tab (lines 225-228) both use ScrollViewer elements with only 8px bottom padding (Padding=\\\"8,14,8,8\\\" and Padding=\\\"8,4,8,8\\\"), which is insufficient to prevent the last line of content from being clipped at the scroll boundary. The developers previously solved this identical bug in StageInputView.axaml (lines 98-105) and StageOutputView.axaml (lines 111-117) by using Margin=\\\"8,8,8,16\\\" on the inner content element rather than relying solely on ScrollViewer.Padding \u2014 with an explicit comment documenting why. That fix was never ported to TaskDetailPanel.axaml's three scrollable tabs (Markdown, Context, Attachments). No auto-scroll-to-bottom or programmatic scroll logic exists in the codebase, so the issue is purely layout-based. The web-CSS solutions suggested in Stage 1 (scroll-padding-bottom, ::after pseudo-elements) do not apply since this is an Avalonia UI app using .axaml markup, not a web app.\",\n  \"constraints\": [\n    \"This is an Avalonia UI (.NET) application using .axaml XAML files \u2014 not a web app \u2014 so CSS properties like scroll-padding-bottom and ::after pseudo-elements do not exist.\",\n    \"The fix must use Avalonia-native layout properties: Padding on the ScrollViewer or Margin on the inner content element.\",\n    \"The established pattern in StageInputView.axaml and StageOutputView.axaml uses a 16px bottom margin on the inner content (ItemsControl) with a comment explaining the technique: 'Inset lives on the content (not ScrollViewer.Padding) so the bottom gap is part of the measured extent and the last item stays reachable.'\",\n    \"Three tabs in TaskDetailPanel.axaml need fixing: Markdown (read-only view, line 146), Context (line 205), and Attachments (line 227).\",\n    \"The Markdown tab also has an edit view (line 154-166) and a new-task view (line 169-201) with TextBox elements \u2014 these may need review too.\",\n    \"The entire TaskDetailPanel is wrapped in a Border with ClipToBounds=\\\"True\\\" (line 9), but this does not affect internal ScrollViewer behavior.\",\n    \"The Markdown read-only ScrollViewer wraps a TextBlock (not ItemsControl), so the margin should be applied to the TextBlock or the ScrollViewer's padding increased.\",\n    \"The Attachments tab ScrollViewer wraps an ItemsControl, matching the StageInputView/StageOutputView pattern exactly.\"\n  ]\n}\n```",
